FBIS4-13931 "drnes079_p_94001" FBIS-NES-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Opposition Attack Repelled in Faryab Province Opposition Attack Repelled in Faryab Province LD2304180194 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304180194 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Pashto BFN [Text] An attack by Dostam's militia was pushed back in (Garzedana) district, Faryab Province. A report from 'Abdol Karim Arshud, a courageous mojahedin commander, says that this morning at 0500 the Dostam militia launched a broad attack against mojahedin positions but the enemy were forced to retreat, leaving 24 dead. The report adds that sixteen militiamen were captured alive by the mojahedin. One combat machine [as heard] and 16 personnel carriers belonging to the enemy were destroyed. The report adds that six militiamen's corpses are still lying on the battlefield. During the fighting, over 20 heroic mojahedin received light injuries.
